ACDS Header

The global header help users understand what the content of the site is about. They appear at the top of a page, above the main body text.

COMPONENT NAME

 

acdsHeader

 


 ANATOMY


Headers are components displayed at the upper top half of the interface. The container component holds other components such as the switcher, header name, search bar and utility icons. Headers can be customized to contain different components that will suit the needs of the users.  



  1. Switcher: Feature that enables user to switch between different portals
  2. Container: Holds all of the components and elements that make up a header
  3. The Header Name: Displays the name of the application or portal the user is currently viewing
  4. Search Bar: Enabling users to find content they’re looking for
  5. Utility Icons: Allows the user to be able to quickly access other key features



USAGE

 

There are two ways to use the Header component:

  • In Experience cloud, from the Component List, drag and drop the Header component onto a page layout slot. To make the component appear in every page, drop the component onto a shared layout slot. Customize the component in the Properties popup.
  • Include the Header component in a custom LWC to feed dynamic data into the component.


The Header component is design to work closely with the Navigation and Footer components to create optimal responsive user experience, they work best when using the ACDS theme layout to arrange the three components together in the Experience cloud environment. See more detail on ACDS them layout.
Site name with default search bar and default action bar

COMPONENT ATTRIBUTES


Name Type Description
title String A site name
appsList Json object Json object for the portal menu
includeSearchBar Boolean Show default search bar
includeActionsBar Boolean Show default action bar


PORTAL MENU JSON ITEM ATTRIBUTES


Name Type Description
text String Item label
link String URL to portal
iconname String Support SLDS utility icon sets (eg: utility:agent_home)


SLOTS


Name Description
search Placeholder for content in the middle of the Header component, eg: search bar.
actions Placeholder for content in right side of the Header component, eg: action bar.


METHODS


Name Description
actionclick Simulates a mouse click on the action icon buttons, event.detail.name values are: Help-Button, Message-Button, Notification-Button

Use Header component inside a LWC to allow the following function:

  • Add event listener for the Search-bar key event
  • Add event listener for Action-bar button click event
  • Add custom content into the search and actions slots
  • Allow dynamic data feed into the component


Template:


  <c-acds-header

    title="ACDS Site header"

    include-search-bar

    include-actions-bar

    onactionclick={handleOnActionButton}

    onkeydown={handleOnKeyDown}

  >

<-- include the follow line to add custom content into the slot placeholders

  <div slot="search">Hello Search Bar</div>

  <div slot="actions">Hellow Actions Bar</div> -->

  </c-acds-header>



Javascript:


  handleOnActionButton(event) {

    console.log(event.detail.name);

  }


  handleOnKeyDown(event) {

    console.log(event.detail.name);

  }
